# Environment Variables Template
# Copy this to .env.local and set your values

# ========================================
# PASSWORD PROTECTION (Optional)
# ========================================
# Uncomment and set a password to enable site-wide password protection
# Leave commented or empty to disable password protection
#
# VITE_ACCESS_PASSWORD=mySecretPassword123

# How it works:
# - If set: Users must enter password to access the site
# - If not set: Site is accessible to everyone
# - Password is stored in sessionStorage (expires when browser closes)
#
# To enable locally:
# 1. Create .env.local file (not tracked by git)
# 2. Add: VITE_ACCESS_PASSWORD=yourPassword
# 3. Restart dev server: npm run dev
#
# To enable on Vercel:
# 1. Go to Vercel Dashboard → Your Project
# 2. Settings → Environment Variables
# 3. Add: VITE_ACCESS_PASSWORD = yourPassword
# 4. Redeploy
# ========================================
